coordinateNotes:
The coordinates come from the label of a wasp separated from this sample and from https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559054. They appear to be UTM 19S (WGS84). They have been converted accordingly (or actually according to EPSG:5389, Peru96 / UTM zone 19S, at https://epsg.io, but this seems to be virtually identical). 
Another alternative would be PSAD 56, the Provisional South American Datum 1956, instead of WGS84 (EPSG:24878 at https://epsg.io). However, its results did not seem to fit the known habitat type of the traps as well as WGS84, nor the files in https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3559054.
